{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:48:40.784Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss surfaces"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (also called loss landscapes) are 3D visualizations of the loss function plotted over the model's parameter space—they show how loss changes as you vary weights, revealing peaks, valleys, flat regions, and the geometry that determines whether gradient descent succeeds, how fast it converges, and whether the solution generalizes to new data."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Loss Surfaces — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a model with parameters "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "θ = (θ₁, θ₂,..., θₙ)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "loss surface"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is defined by:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "L(θ) = loss value for parameter combination θ"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In words"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": For every possible value of θ, you get a corresponding loss value, forming a surface."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Geometric visualization:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine a terrain with hills and valleys:\n- Height (z-axis) = loss value\n- Position (x, y axes) = parameter values\n\nThe lowest point on the surface = optimal parameters (minimum loss) [web:262][web:265]\n\nFor 2 parameters:\n       z (Loss)\n       |\n       |     /  ← Loss surface L(θ₁, θ₂)\n       |    /   Valley = minimum\n       |___/____ θ₁\n      /\n     θ₂\n\nGradient points uphill; negative gradient points downhill [web:259]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key analogy:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient descent on a loss surface = hiking down a mountain blindfolded"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- You feel the slope (gradient) at your feet\n- You step downhill (opposite to gradient)\n- You repeat until you reach the bottom (minimum)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The shape of the loss landscape determines:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it affects optimization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth, convex surfaces → gradient descent succeeds easily"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Steep slopes → faster convergence; flat regions → slow"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generalization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Flat minima → better generalization; sharp minima → overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Difficulty"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Saddles, ravines, local minima → harder to optimize"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In training GPT-4 with billions of parameters, the loss surface exists in billion-dimensional space; we study 2D slices to understand optimization geometry."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key features of loss surfaces"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convex vs. Non-convex"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convex loss surface"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "      /\n     /\n    /   ← Bowl shape (single global minimum)\n   /\n  /\n\nProperties:\n- Single global minimum\n- Any local minimum = global minimum\n- Gradient descent always succeeds [web:261][web:262]\n\nExample: Linear regression with MSE loss"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-convex loss surface"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (neural networks):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "  /\\    /\\\n /  \\  /  \\   ← Multiple valleys, hills\n/    \\/    \\\n\nProperties:\n- Multiple local minima\n- Some minima not globally optimal\n- Gradient descent may get stuck [web:262]\n\nExample: Neural network training (deep learning)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Minima types"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Generalization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Global minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lowest point on entire surface"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best (optimal loss)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Local minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lowest in neighborhood, but not globally"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "May be worse"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sharp minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Narrow valley, steep sides"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Poor generalization (overfits)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Flat minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Wide valley, gentle slopes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Better generalization"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why flat minima generalize better"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Flat minimum: Small weight changes → small loss change → robust to noise\nSharp minimum: Small weight changes → large loss change → sensitive to noise [web:261]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Saddle points"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "      ___\n     /   \\   ← Saddle: flat in one direction, curved in another\n    /     \\\n\nProperties:\n- Gradient ≈ 0 (looks like minimum)\n- But not minimum: can go lower in some direction\n- Common in high-dimensional spaces [web:261]\n\nProblem: Gradient descent slows down at saddles (gradient ≈ 0)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ravines"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "    /|\\\n   / | \\   ← Long, narrow valley (steep sides, gentle bottom)\n  /  |  \\\n\nProblem: Gradient oscillates across ravine (zigzagging)\nSolution: Use momentum or adaptive methods (Adam) [web:261]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient Descent on Loss Surfaces"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Algorithm:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Initialize parameters: θ₀ (random)\n\nFor t = 0, 1, 2, ...:\n    1. Compute gradient: ∇L(θₜ)\n    2. Update: θₜ₊₁ = θₜ - η × ∇L(θₜ)\n    \nWhere:\n- η = learning rate (step size)\n- Gradient points uphill; negative gradient points downhill [web:265]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visual flow:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start at θ₀ = [4, 5] (high loss, top of hill)\n   ↓\nCompute gradient at θ₀\n   ↓\nStep downhill: θ₁ = θ₀ - η × ∇L(θ₀)\n   ↓\nRepeat until gradient ≈ 0 (at minimum) [web:265]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Gradient Descent:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇L(θ) = (1/N) × Σᵢ₌₁ᴺ ∇Lᵢ(θ)  (average gradient over ALL N samples)\n\nPros: Stable, deterministic\nCons: Slow for large datasets (must compute all N gradients) [web:260]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇L(θ) ≈ ∇Lᵢ(θ)  (gradient from ONE randomly chosen sample i)\n\nPros: Fast, works for large datasets\nCons: Hops around path to minimum (noisy) [web:259][web:260]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD behavior"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LS path: Hops around, zigzags toward minimum\nGD path: Smooth, direct path to minimum\n\nSGD \"hops around\" on its path to the minimum on the loss surface [web:259]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mini-batch SGD (practical compromise):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "∇L(θ) = (1/B) × Σᵢ₌₁ᴬ ∇Lᵢ(θ)  (average over batch of B samples, e.g., B = 32)\n\nBalances stability (GD) and speed (SGD) [web:260][web:266]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning Rate Schedules"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "learning rate η"}, {"type": "text", "text": " controls step size on the loss surface. Choosing the right schedule is critical for convergence."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Constant Learning Rate"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η = 0.01 (fixed throughout training)\n\nPros: Simple\nCons: May overshoot minimum or converge too slowly [web:260]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step Decay"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η = 0.1 until epoch 10, then η = 0.01 until epoch 20, then η = 0.001\n\nReduce LR by factor (e.g., 10×) at fixed epochs [web:266]\n\nPros: Large steps early, fine-tuning later\nCons: Requires knowing when to decay"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Inverse Scaling"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(t) = η₀ / t^(power_t)\n\nFor regression: η(t) = η₀ / t^(power_t) [web:260]\n\nPros: Automatic decay\nCons: Slower early convergence"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cosine Annealing"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(t) = η_min + (η_max - η_min) × (1 + cos(π × t/T)) / 2\n\nLR follows cosine curve from max to min over T epochs [web:266]\n\nPros: Smooth decay, often achieves better accuracy\nCons: Requires tuning T"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning Rate Warmup"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start with small η, increase to max, then decrease:\n\nη(t) = small → η_max → η_min\n\nPopularized by fast.ai; often achieves same accuracy in fewer epochs [web:266]\n\nPros: Prevents early divergence, improves convergence\nCons: Adds complexity"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive Decay (Validation-based)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluate held-out set after each epoch\nAnneal LR when validation loss change < threshold\n\nTends to give good convergence to local optima [web:263]\n\nPros: Automatic, adaptive to training progress\nCons: Requires validation set"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Comparison: GD vs SGD vs Mini-batch"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Method"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Convergence speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Stability"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All N samples"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slow (large N)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High (smooth)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small datasets"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1 sample"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Low (noisy)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very large datasets"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mini-batch"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "B samples (e.g., 32)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Moderate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Most practical cases"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss surface = terrain"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Height = loss, position = parameters"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convex"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Single global minimum; gradient descent always succeeds"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-convex"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Multiple local minima; may get stuck (deep learning)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Flat minima"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Better generalization; sharp minima: overfitting"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Saddle points"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient ≈ 0 but not minimum; common in high dimensions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ravines"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cause zigzagging; use momentum/Adam"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient descent"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": θ = θ - η × ∇L(θ) (step downhill)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SGD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uses 1 sample; hops around path to minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Mini-batch"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Uses B samples (e.g., 32); balances stability and speed"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate schedules"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Constant, step decay, inverse scaling, cosine annealing, warmup"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, understanding loss surfaces is fundamental: the geometry of billion-parameter optimization determines whether GPT trains successfully, how flat vs. sharp minima affect generalization, and why learning rate schedules like cosine annealing improve convergence in practice."}]}]}}